Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRiS
Vol / Page:  251
Edition:
Quote:  <i>kohua,  n. </i>Maori word, for (1) a Maori oven; (2) a boiler. There is a Maori <i>verb Kohu</i>, to cook or steam in a native oven (from a noun <i>Kohu</i>, steam, mist), and an <i>adj. Kohu</i>, concave. The word is used by the English in New Zealand, and is said to be the origin of <i>Goashore (qv.). </i>
