Author:  BURTON
Vol / Page:  1
Edition:
Quote:  The third method, boiling (or <i>kohua</i>), seems to have been used more rarely. Because the Maori did not make pottery, their only means of heating a liquid was by dropping a red-hot stone into a wooden bowl containing the liquid.
